26/05/2009
TIRANA, Albania -- The state will offer funding to political parties running in the June parliamentary elections, earmarking about 500,000 euros for the effort, local media reported on Monday (May 25th). The biggest party in parliament -- the ruling Democratic Party -- will receive about 113,000 euros, as it won most parliament seats in the 2005 elections. The main opposition Socialist Party will get about 90,000 euros, followed by the Republican Party and the Social Democratic Party. Campaign season officially begins on Thursday and runs one month. (Shekulli, Top Channel, Ora News, Balkan Insight - 25/05/09)
